question: When taken to a new habitat, non-native plants often threaten native plants of the new habitat. Why do non-native plants threaten native plants?
candidate_answers: (A) Non-native plants are able to mutate rapidly. (B) Non-native plants cause native animals to relocate. (C) Non-native plants are able to be used for medicine. (D) Non-native plants compete with native plants for resources.
answer: Non-native plants are able to be used for medicine.
label: C
